    • Constructor Detail

      • CreateSwarmServiceInfo

        public CreateSwarmServiceInfo(java.lang.String image,
                      java.lang.String name,
                      float cpus,
                      int memMBytes,
                      int replicas,
                      int targetPort,
                      int publishPort)
        Non Default Constructor to specify a Swarm Service creation information.
        Parameters:
        image - The Image Name.
        name - The Swarm Service Name.
        cpus - The CPU's in a percent, the Docker API requires a CPU quota in units of 10 to the 9th CPUs, default is 500000, so take the desired CPU's and divide by / 1000000000.
        memMBytes - The Memory in Mbytes, the Docker API requires bytes so multiply this by 1000000.
        replicas - The number of replicas to create in the Swarm.
        targetPort - The Target Port inside the Container.
        publishPort - The Published Port outside the Container.
